18.785 | Number Theory I | http://ocw.mit.edu/courses/mathematics/18-785-analytic-number-theory-spring-2007 | level:Graduate features:Lecture notes, Assignments (no solutions) prereq:none. coreq:18.705 instructors:A. Sutherland term:G (Fall) textbook:Davenport, H., and H. L. Montgomery. Multiplicative Number Theory. New York, NY: Springer-Verlag, 2000. textbook:Iwaniec, Henryk, and Emmanuel Kowalski. Analytic Number Theory. Providence, RI: American Mathematical Society, 2004.  description:Dedekind domains, unique factorization of ideals, splitting of primes. Lattice methods, finiteness of the class group, Dirichlet's unit theorem. Local fields, ramification, discriminants. Zeta and L-functions, analytic class number formula. Adeles and ideles. Statements of class field theory and the Chebotarev density theorem.  3-0-9 units
