18.952 | Theory of Differential Forms | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=18.952 Theory of Differential Forms | prereq:18.101 18.700 or 18.701 instructors:V. W. Guillemin term:U (Spring) description:Multilinear algebra: tensors and exterior forms. Differential forms on R n : exterior differentiation, the pull-back operation and the Poincaré lemma. Applications to physics: Maxwell's equations from the differential form perspective. Integration of forms on open sets of R n . The change of variables formula revisited. The degree of a differentiable mapping. Differential forms on manifolds and De Rham theory. Integration of forms on manifolds and Stokes' theorem. The push-forward operation for forms. Thom forms and intersection theory. Applications to differential topology.  3-0-9 units
